                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Ok so Im lvl 65 190aas and I still enjoy pick up groups. I think its fun to meet new ppl. Anyways I dont have a guild so im pretty much forced to do pick up groups :p
<br />

<br />
So here I was doing a normal LDoN slaughter mission. Group consisted of warrior warrior cleric druid wizard and me. We get all buffed up, I tell the group that i will be puller. The MT was a little surprised but others in the group were used to ENc/Bard pullers so there was np.
<br />

<br />
About 3 or 4 kills in the MT asks if I have Nights Dark Terror. Now heres where the conflict began. I told him yes I had it but I didnt have a spell slot free to keep it memmed.(if i would have just lied and said I didnt have the spell like i usually do none of this would have happened) I told him i would give him werewolf or any other illusion he wanted as long as it didnt take up a slot. 
<br />

<br />
His reply: Other than mez and slow what spells do you even use.
<br />
My reply: Rune Mez Tash Slow Root Stun Charm Pacify
<br />
MT: YOu dont need root or stun. Give me my buff
<br />
Me: How am I supposed to recharm without stun? How am I supposed to med without root or pally MT?
<br />
Druid: pwned
<br />
MT: If you would give me the buffs I ask for I will be able to taunt and then u can med. And when did I say you could charm anyways? Imo charm is a good way to get us all killed. God I hate chanters that dont give you buffs when u ask for them.
<br />
Me: Dude you have NFC about playing an enchanter, Im pulling mezzing slowing and charming, all u have to do is turn on attack and you have the nerve to try and tell me how to play my char? Ok fine baby just to make you shut up ill lose root and put up your stupid pumpkin head buff.
<br />
MT: You shouldnt be an enchanter you dont know what you are doing.
<br />
Me: Sorry but I dont have the spell summon: baby bottle or id cast that for ya too.
<br />
Cleric: Both of you shut up or im leaving.
<br />

<br />
At this point I cast the stupid NDT and he shut up. The group went on to win the mission np, I kept pulling slowing and mezzing. Held a pet the entire time. I was especially careful not to make any mistakes knowing that the warrior was just looking for a reason to say "I told ya so". Everything went smoothly and the cleric even sent me a tell saying she was impressed.
<br />

<br />
I dunno what my point was for typing this but that guy really got under my skin. Enchanters can be played a ton of different ways, I have my style and others have theirs. I would think that at lvl 65 ppl would stop telling you how to play. At lvl 65 with nearly 200aas I have at least earned that.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
