                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Arent you being just as bad? You are dictating to the warrios how his class works.  Warrior's point is he is a better war with NDT. He can hold agro better and put out more DPS as a pumpkin.  The group trade off is NDT versus the added security/med time root brings.  Shouldn't it be up to the group to decide which alternative to use?  
<br />

<br />
In terms of Charm, while its fun, there is an added danger to using it.  For people who are very concerned with their win% charm might be an unnecessary risk.  Personally I tell people before I enter a pick up group I will be pulling & charming so they can find another chanter if they wont one who doesnt want risk.
<br />

<br />
And BTW I often ignore NDT, the spell is no fun to cast and the 5-10% increase in melee DPS is not enough to justify its use to me.  Thats just because im lazy though.
