                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">No one ever likes being told about there class...specially in front of others. While it started in group chat, it really could have moved to tells. In pickup groups, I think it is very important to make sure roles are known. One suggestion I would make is to always check ahead of time what buffs people need (besides the std candy and hastes). I think the warrior should have worked everything out with you prior to entering. However, you did have 3 other root classes in the group and as far as I have seen, LDoN mobs dont summon (only 60 and only been to NRo and BB adventure), so druid root works perfectly fine whereever root is needed (think druid would be ideal to serve as the root caster...wizzies are weaker and cleric has other concerns).
<br />

<br />
An alternative I use to stun is to just use mez (at this point its GoK). It takes the pet out of the fight longer, but that is really one fight for a normal group (in my LDoN experiences). Fairly fast cast time and since I lack any spell hastes/extended range, it buys me all the time I need.
<br />

<br />
Side Note - doesnt an extra spell gem seem so nice at 61+ (since rune basically goes from rarely used, save raids, to highly useful). Once upon a time I had 2 or 3 slots that I could use for anything, but that is quickly dropping (specially since I have found the beauty of charming in groups).</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=583742" target="_blank" class="postlink">Phreza Bum</a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
