                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">NDT is worthless for aggro purposes, and Lone_War is correct in that Trickster's would have been better for that reason - and still only a marginal benefit.  The simple fact is, he was being an arrogant hothead and forcing you to give up a spell slot.  Basically, he wanted you to give something up that was vital to you (a spell slot) for a small (questionable) benefit to him.  You could have said "Ok, fine, but take off your armor because to me you look better without it."  A warrior's armor is vital just like a caster's spell slots are vital.
<br />

<br />
When the warrior asked "Other than mez and slow what spells do you even use?" that would have been the end of it right there for me personally.  He was setting out to be a jerk (if the conversation really went as you described here) and if at level 65ish he thinks that NDT is going to be that big of a deal for his aggro - he is in NO position to be telling someone else how to play.  There are some rare situations where I can drop a spell to afford a long recast / short duration like NDT or trickster, but the majority of the time there are much better ways to fill spell slots.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=659405" target="_blank" class="postlink">Xerys, Tier`dal Coercer, Bertoxxulous</a> ~Retired~</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
