                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">Arent you being just as bad? You are dictating to the warrios how his class works. Warrior's point is he is a better war with NDT. He can hold agro better and put out more DPS as a pumpkin. The group trade off is NDT versus the added security/med time root brings. Shouldn't it be up to the group to decide which alternative to use? 
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />

<br />
Hmm actually no its not up to the group to decide what spells I mem. Its up to me to decide that based on my experience as an enchanter.
<br />

<br />
Turn it around and look at it like this: I certainly wouldnt be part of a group that wanted to vote on what spells the cleric has memmed. Im an enchanter and I dont know jack about being a cleric or what spells they need. My vote would be ignorant in that situation. In the same way that a warriors or rangers vote would be ignorant in regards to my spells.
<br />

<br />
Anytime you group with ppl there is a certain amount of trust involved. Each class depends on the others. I cant do my job without heals, or melees to tank. I trust the ppl in my group to do their jobs. If they dont then I dont group with them again, or at least not seek them out. If i make mistakes (and oh boy ive made some doosies) I wouldnt expect that person to seek me out the next time. 
<br />

<br />
Its all about trust. If you dont have that then the group is setting itself up for failure.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
