                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">i only use root myself when farming solo, or dueling. most mobs i fight now-days summon. rooting a summoning mob don't do much; i know, i know. there is a bugg where if you root a mob that summons, it will attack the closest person and not summon you(usually). but, that also hurts your unsuspecting rogue, bard, ect when the mob suddenly starts smacking them around-as we all know that when a mob it rooted, it attacks the closest PC, regardless of aggro.
<br />

<br />
nothing wrong with using root. nothing at all. everyone has their own tactic. i just don't use it often. i don't sit in LDoN too much. get some pot9, mixed with my C5 and my UMR (unbuffed mana regen) of 7, i don't feel it too badly. i still med when i can, though.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Hipna Tyze, Coecer on Luclin
