                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well:
<br />

<br />
- Root is my most used form of CC, always has been.  With POP and -30 MR roots that last 3+ minutes I like root even more now.
<br />

<br />
- I approach my CC a little differently than the popular enchanter approach.
<br />

<br />
I attempt to drive my aggro as high as possible on a mob vs the common approach of dumping aggro which generally means:
<br />

<br />
1. Greater Fetter
<br />
2. Tash
<br />
3. Slow
<br />

<br />
I will mezz where I have to but it will generally be followed by the above and the mezz will generally not be renewed.
<br />

<br />
I group almost exclusively with a warrior and I find between this and a charmed pet that I can drive the warrior's aggro up very high on his taunt which aids him in securing aggro against a mob and allows the rest of the group to pump out more damage without drawing aggro.
<br />

<br />
As for the behaviour of rooted summoning mobs ... I have never considered aggro management via root a bug, I have always considered it expected behaviour ... it has been in the game since day 1, they are aware of it and never stated it was a bug.  Either way aggro management via root is one of the largest reasons I use root.
<br />

<br />
Generally people wait a short time while the tank secures aggro before opening up barring slow and what is necessary to get slow to land.  During this time, Root does a great job of artifically focusing the mob aggro on the MT until the MT secures aggro at which point your root inevitably gets broken by a nuke <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
As for it hurting another melee, if they have not learned how to fight at max melee yet then perhaps they should learn ... it is a pretty general concept.  You warn them upfront and if they do not listen then they take a few hits and learn.
<br />

<br />
Root is cheaper on mana, lands easier than mezz due to the -30MR adjustment and lasts longer than mezz does on average, it does not blur which mezz can do and helps to focus aggro when used correctly.
<br />

<br />
My lineup is generally:
<br />

<br />
1. Charm or Nuke
<br />
2. Slow
<br />
3. Scryers
<br />
4. Stun
<br />
5. Mezz
<br />
6. Arcane Rune
<br />
7. Tash/Buff slot
<br />
8. Greater Fetter
<br />

<br />
Regards,</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />Sage <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=370213" target="_blank" class="postlink">Zanithar TideBreaker</a> - Coercer
<br />
<a href="http://www.therelentless.com" target="_blank" class="postlink">The Relentless</a>, Cazic Thule</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
